commitmsg: Fixes lint/validation errors.
Moves all view logic into angular
Changes endpoint url so that it's more descriptive.
Moves front end to Angular

Fix up clobberer api tests

Adds tests for all endpoints.
Fixes clobber request test, so that it reflects the new API.

Create REST endpoints for serving UI relevant data

Favors building a UI with angular rather rather than by using flask template logic.
Adds a new interface for retreiving clobber times.

Finishes the skeleton of clobberer_branch UI

The most stable change is the sqlalchemy query which
fetches all relevant ui data (buildername, builddir, max(lastclobber), who)
Simplifies the clobber request interface by removing superflous data. The model retains unused fields for database compatibility.
A simple way to get to a branch's specific clobberer selection page.
A placeholder for the eventual UI. Buildername and branch are useful for debugging.
Adds new UI endpoints and context.
Bump version by +0.0.1

Merge pull request #3 from mrrrgn/forceclob2

Adds an endpoint which will always result in a clobber when accessed by ...

Adds an endpoint which will always result in a clobber when accessed by the client

Some builders are configured in such a way as to always require clobbering,
this is currently acheived by pointing them at the endpoint provided by:
https://github.com/mozilla/build-tools/blob/master/clobberer/always_clobber.php
Which simply returns a lastclobber time of the current time + one hour.
The forceclobber endpoint re-implements this behavior.

Revert some sed of skeleton in validate.sh

This was from https://github.com/mozilla/build-relengapi-skeleton/ and per IRC with @djmitche is not intended to be sed changed.

Merge pull request #36 from mrrrgn/authfix

Bug 1164878 - Allow users without an authenticated_email field to clo…

Bug 1164878 - Allow users without an authenticated_email field to clobber

The TokenUser is not anonymous, but also has no e-mail address associated with it.
When this combination occurs, a who value of 'automation' should be supplied, instead
of outright failing.

While not exact, the term automation gives us a way to categorize clobbers that seemed
to be authenticated by a permanent token (as opposed to a user token).

Merge pull request #6 from mrrrgn/clobber-logic

Clobber logic
Adds clarifying comment.
Gets rid of the nasty sleep in the tests.
Fixes a comment typo.
Cleaning up formatting and comments.
pep8 fix from validate.sh

Adds the ability to clobber specific slaves

The clobber endpoint now supports passing in a specific slave, when a slave is specified
only lastclobber queries with that slave will have access to its clobbertime. Otherwise,
when no slave is specified, a NULL value is passed to the clobber_times table and any
slave will have access to its data. That is, NULL acts as a wildcard for slaves.
Changes dependency on relengapi to >= 1.0 for angular support.
Bump version to 0.2.0

Merge pull request #4 from mrrrgn/ui

This adds an angular based ui to the new clobberer back end.
Breaks up a test that was too large.
Removes superflous error checking.

Better handling of empty states

When branchData is initilized it should default to a 'loading' state,
when the api returns a 404 it should let the user know that no data was
retrieved. The clobber button should also only be available when there
is data available for it to submit (i.e. boxes are checked).
Removes un-necessary select all from ui. This is a common form pattern and does not need pointing out.

Remove un-necessary url_for's

The API should remain relatively stable. All the url_for's aren't adding enough value to justify the work involved in using them.
typo: Used templates where static was called for.

Validate.sh Fixes

setup.py was missing the angular html in clobberer/static and imports needed reordering.
Minor style tweaks.
Avoiding clashing fonts within relengapi.
Adds pretty styling to the clobberer table.
Just adds whitespace for formatting.
Using unicode(current_user) leads to awkward formatting and junk colons which need to be stripped out. This logic properly handles the assignment of user names to the 'who' field in a ClobberTime.
Removes hard coded url from the angular controller.
Fixes lastclobber by branch query so that it attaches the corrent 'who' to the max lastclobber.
